==Scottish Gaelic==
===Preposition===
'''ri'''

#[[with]]
#Used before a noun or verbal noun to mean "up to" or "involved in"
#*''Bha clann sin ri mì-mhodh.'' (These children were up to no-good.)
#In the [[w:Lewis|Lewis]] dialect, ''ri'' is used instead of ''ag'' or ''a''' before a verbal noun to form participles
#*''Tha mi '''ri''' seinn.'' (I am singing - as opposed to ''Tha mi '''a'''' seinn'', which has the same meaning)
[[Category:Scots Gaelic prepositions]]

